A couple of newlyweds were pulled over by the police on the way to their reception – when their driver sounded an illegal air horn.

Ali, 34, and Paul Bartlett, 43, from Weymouth, were on their way to their wedding reception after tying the knot in Portland Castle, Dorset, in a replica Dodge Charger.

The car, which was manufactured by the Dodge division of Chrysler, is a vehicle in the 80s TV show Dukes of Hazzard.

