Mr Bartlett said: ‘When he asked Wayne to open the bonnet it all started to look very serious.

‘I thought he was going to be given a warning I did not think it would be a full summons.'

The couple were allowed to continue their journey to the wedding reception.

Mr Bartlett said: ‘I have to say it did make a talking point at the reception and I think we will always remember the day when our wedding car was stopped by the police. They did not even apologise to Ali on her big day.’

Dorset police issued a summons for Mr Duke to attend court.

Mr Duke, from Wimborne, says he did not realise his Dixie horn was illegal.

He said: ‘I do have a normal horn but it’s such a fun car that everybody loves the ‘Dixie Land’ horn and beg me to sound it.’

